Ghana Oil Rises First Day in Two Weeks on Dividend Declaration

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-06-10T13:11:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/ghana-oil-rises-first-day-in-two-weeks-on-dividend-declaration.html
Ghana Oil Co., which runs a network
of gasoline stations in the West African nation, rose for the
first time in almost two weeks as it declared a dividend of
0.012 cedi per share for the year ended December 2010.  The stock climbed 1 pesewa, or 3.3 percent, to 31 pesewas
by 1:02 p.m. in the capital, Accra, the first increase since May
30.  The company, also known as Goil, will pay the dividend on
July 25, it said in a statement published on the website of the
Ghana Stock Exchange today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 